Context:
SPIKE TEST CONFIRMED: Chrome strips custom manifest.json fields, so we CANNOT use manifest.json. Instead, we embed the hash as `window.__EXTENSION_HASH__` in the side panel JS bundle. This was verified in an E2E spike test — the side panel can read it via `(window as any).__EXTENSION_HASH__` and it stays frozen in memory even after disk changes.

The build pipeline runs in this order (from root package.json build script):
1. `tsc --build`
2. `npm run generate:browser-tools-catalog`
3. `npm run --prefix platform/browser-extension build:bundle` (bundles background.js + offscreen/index.js)
4. `npm run --prefix platform/browser-extension build:side-panel` (bundles side-panel.js + styles.css)
5. `tsx scripts/generate-icons.ts`
6. `tsx scripts/install-extension.ts` (copies to ~/.opentabs/extension/)

The hash script must run AFTER step 4 (all bundles exist) but BEFORE step 6 (files are copied). Insert it between steps 5 and 6 (or between 4 and 5 — icons don't affect runtime).

Read the root package.json first to see the exact build script chain.

Changes:

1. Create `scripts/compute-extension-hash.ts`:
```typescript
import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';
import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';
import { join } from 'node:path';

const extDir = join(import.meta.dirname, '..', 'platform', 'browser-extension');

// Hash the key runtime files (order matters for determinism)
const filesToHash = [
  'dist/background.js',
  'dist/side-panel/side-panel.js',
  'dist/side-panel/styles.css',
  'dist/offscreen/index.js',
];

const hash = createHash('sha256');
for (const file of filesToHash) {
  hash.update(readFileSync(join(extDir, file)));
}
const extensionHash = hash.digest('hex').slice(0, 16);

// 1. Write hash file for the server to read
writeFileSync(join(extDir, '.extension-hash'), extensionHash + '\n');

// 2. Prepend hash assignment to side panel bundle
const sidePanelPath = join(extDir, 'dist', 'side-panel', 'side-panel.js');
const sidePanelJs = readFileSync(sidePanelPath, 'utf-8');
writeFileSync(sidePanelPath, `window.__EXTENSION_HASH__="${extensionHash}";\n${sidePanelJs}`);

console.log(`  Extension hash: ${extensionHash}`);
```

